Transactions are logged, and digital signatures captured for use in autogenerating documentation, such as form 0751. This lesson covers community and role responsibilities in the Asset Turn In process. For more information about the process, please go to App

or use in autogenerating documentation, such as form 0751. This lesson covers community and role responsibilities in the Asset Turn In process. For more information about the process, please go to Appendix A - Turn In Asset Business Process to view the flowchart and process narrative. ## User Roles and Responsibilities The audience for this training includes the following user roles: | Role | Responsibility | |------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | Custodial Official | Certifies asset inventory lists (EILs); approves requests for Asset turn-ins and Reports of Survey; assigns Custodial Official alternates | | HTM Admin | Classifies Assets; reviews and approves Work Orders; creates PMs (pr

ory lists (EILs); approves requests for Asset turn-ins and Reports of Survey; assigns Custodial Official alternates | | HTM Admin | Classifies Assets; reviews and approves Work Orders; creates PMs (preventive maintenance); approves PM work deferrals; creates Job Plans; determines need for decontamination and/or special handling of turned in Assets | | HTM Tech Plus | Performs work, identifies need to defer work, and updates PM work status, work reassignment | | HTM Tech | Performs work and completes Work Orders, identifies need to defer work; updates PM work status; performs decontamination and/or performing special handling of sensitive devices; Work Orders on turned in Assets | | HTM Work Order Clerk | Reviews and evaluates Service Requests; plans and approves work and assigns Work Orders to HTM shops | | Information Security Officer (ISO) | Certifies Asset sanitization is completed appropriately | | IT Tech | Manages certain data on IT assets and prints barcode labels; performs spec

s to HTM shops | | Information Security Officer (ISO) | Certifies Asset sanitization is completed appropriately | | IT Tech | Manages certain data on IT assets and prints barcode labels; performs special handling of sensitive turned in Assets, and completes associated Work Orders | | NX Admin | Creates new Asset records (individually or in bulk using Asset templates); runs EIL reports; updates Asset location and last inventory date; processes and records Asset turn ins and disposition; updates the indication of whether an asset is sensitive; manages/coordinates report of survey Work Orders | | NX Tech | Creates new equipment records individually; runs EIL reports and updates location and last inventory date for Assets; retrieves, processes and | | | records Asset turn ins and disposition; manages/coordinates Report of Survey Work Orders, updates the indication of whether an asset is sensitive | |------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Supervisors for IT Assets (78 series) are IT Supervisors and will need to have that role; Supervisors for biomedical Assets are anyone with the HTM Admin role. | ## Learning Objectives - · Describe the Asset Turn In Process - · Create an Asset Turn In Service Request - · Approve an Asset Turn In Service Request - · Reject Asset Turn In Service Request - · Review Asset Turn In Work Order for Appropriate Action - · Complete Work Required to Enable Asset Turn In - · Verify Sanitization if Required - · Certify Assets Requiring Sanitization - · Complete Asset T

Should any Role not have an individual provisioned in it, the Turn In process is not pressed correctly and the flow of the work order will stall. ## ROLE ## PERSON GROUPS Description ISO ISO Tech IMPORTANT! Local Site Support should be contacted if individuals need to be provisioned as required to allow a seamless

## ROLE ## PERSON GROUPS Description ISO ISO Tech IMPORTANT! Local Site Support should be contacted if individuals need to be provisioned as required to allow a seamless flow of the Asset Turn In process. ## ASSET SANITIZATION CERTIFICATION (ISO) The Information Security Officer must certify that Asset(s) marked as a Sensitive Item must have had all work completed prior to being picked up by PPM. Step 1. From the Inbox/Assignments portlet on the Start Center , select the appropriate Certify Sanitization of Assets on WO. Figure 1. Inbox/Assignments Portlet Step 1. The Work Order opens in Work Order Tracking on the Work Order tab. Click the Route Workflow icon tool bar to accept responsibility. Figure 2. Route Work Flow Icon - Step 2. The Complete Workflow Assignment dialog box appears to Accept Responsibility to Certify Sanitization . Select the OK button. - Step 3. Scroll down to the Multiple Assets, Locations and CIs section.

The Complete Workflow Assignment dialog box appears to Accept Responsibility to Certify Sanitization . Select the OK button. - Step 3. Scroll down to the Multiple Assets, Locations and CIs section. Clicking the View Details - icon to the left of the first item listed. Figure 3. Complete Workflow Assignment Dialog Box Figure 4. Multiple Assets, Locations and CIs Section - View Details Icon Step 4. The Details section will display, and the icon will change to a Close Details . Review/verify the information in the Details section. Perform any physical validation needed on the assets listed. Repeat this for each item listed. NOTE: Values listed under Configuration Items are hard drives that have been removed and have had work performed on them. NOTE: A partially completed Equipment Sanitization Certificate (0751) can be printed to have a list of hard drives reported on the 0751 to help with the certification activity. The Manual Input dialog box appears. Information can be entered the Memo field (optional) then click the OK button: - · Approve and Send to PPM : Certifies all required work has been completed and forwards the Work Order to PPM for appropriate action. - · Return to Responsible Department for Additional Work : Identifies additional work which is required before certification can be provided. Returns the Work Order back to the Responsible Department to take appropriate action. - Step 7. The completed Equipment Sanitization Certificate

The 0751 will not be fully populated until certification is completed by the ISO. This report lists Configuration Items (hard drives) only and will not list the Assets. ## PRINTING TURN IN FORM (2237) The Turn In Form (2237) report can be printed from the Turn In Work Order in the Work Order application at any point; however, will not be fully populate until PPM picks up the Asset(s) and finalizes there Turn In process. This report lists Assets only and will not list Configuration Items (hard drives). Those are listed on the Equipment Sanitization Certificate (0751) report. IMPORTANT! The Work Order MUST BE a Turn In Work Order and have at least one Asset. Configuration Items will not be printed on the Turn In Form (2237), only the EIL Asset(s). - Step 1. From the Work Order Tracking application and on an Asset Turn In Work Order , click on the Select Action and select Run Reports . - Step 2. The Reports and Schedules dialog box opens. In the Description filter field, enter 2237 and press the enter key on the key board. Select Turn In Form (2237) . Figure 14. Work Order Tracking Application Figure 15.

If turn in request is valid, proceed to step 1.4.3. If the turn in request is not valid, proceed to step 1.4.11. | | 1.4.3 | The Responsible Department (which may be FM, HTM, or IT) receives a work order and manually handles any necessary pre-turn in work if needed. Note: If the Responsible Department on the assets being turned in is HTM or FM then the turn in work order will go to HTM or FM accordingly. If the assets being turned in are on a 78 series EIL AND if at least one of the assets on the work order is marked as a Sensitive Item, then the work order will go to IT. In any other cases, the work order will go directly to PPM.

are on a 78 series EIL AND if at least one of the assets on the work order is marked as a Sensitive Item, then the work order will go to IT. In any other cases, the work order will go directly to PPM. Note: If the Responsible Department of the asset(s) on the work order is HTM or FM, the HTM Admin or FM WO Clerk may first choose to delegate the work to and HTM Tech or an FM Tech. If the ass et(s) on the work order are IT assets (on a 78 series EIL), the IT Tech will begin execution of any work needed. Examples of pre-turn in work include decontamination/wipe down of an asset, purging or removal of fluids, environmental management (such as cleaning hospital beds), ensuring safe disposal of specialized assets (such as radioactive or other contaminates), cleaning lab equipment containing reagents, removing freon from and defrosting refrigerators, uninstalling a piece of equipment. | | 1.4.4 | If the asset(s) on the work order require data sanitization (e.g.

ng lab equipment containing reagents, removing freon from and defrosting refrigerators, uninstalling a piece of equipment. | | 1.4.4 | If the asset(s) on the work order require data sanitization (e.g., removal of hard drives). Asset Turn In Business Process Narrative | Step Number | Description | |---------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | 1.4.5 | In Maximo, the Responsible Department will record the sanitization activity for any asset(s) that underwent data sanitization

---------------------------------------------------------------| | 1.4.5 | In Maximo, the Responsible Department will record the sanitization activity for any asset(s) that underwent data sanitization. This includes creating a Configuration Item within the work order for each hard drive removed from an asset and recording the date the hard drive was removed. If any assets on the turn in work order underwent data sanitization, proceed to step 1.4.6. that the asset(s) on the work order were sanitized appropriately, once all physical review has been completed. | | 1.4.8 | Once the sanitization is certified by the ISO, Maximo informs Logistics (Admin (NX), Tech (NX)). | | 1.4.9 | The Admin (NX), Tech (NX) physically retrieves the assets. | | 1.4.10 | Using Maximo, the Admin (NX), Tech (NX) records the turn in of the asset(s) on the work order (e.g., assigns Action Codes to the assets within the work order) and closes the work order. Closing the work order automatically sets the asset(s) status to TURN IN and sets the asset(s) EIL to 991. The process ends until the asset(s) are ready for final disposition. | | 1.4.11 | The Service Requestor receives notification from Maximo that the service request was rejected. |
